                        Minister in Switzerland (
                        Harrison
                    )Repeated to Chungking, Moscow, and
                        London as telegrams 1259, 1836, and 6912, respectively.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d443</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">443</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-14T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-14T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-14T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="443" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9454/8–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="95" xml:id="d443fn1">Repeated to Chungking, Moscow, and
                        London as telegrams 1259, 1836, and 6912, respectively.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-14T20:00:00-04:00">August 14, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2535. See Dept’s cirtel concerning Japanese archives.<note n="96" xml:id="d443fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> Request Swiss to communicate following to the Japanese Govt: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Japanese Govt will immediately instruct its diplomatic and consular
                            offices in neutral countries to surrender custody of all property and
                            archives to representatives of Allied powers.</p>
                        <p>The Japanese Govt will likewise authorize the appropriate government
                            protecting its interests to relinquish diplomatic and consular property
                            and archives to the custody of Allied powers in belligerent
                            countries.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
